just for anybody looking, much of this music is almost universally wrong. from the time i've spent studying the sheets for "boogie woogie stomp" i've come to find that almost none of the notes are correct. some of them are vaguely in the right area, and sometimes the left hand is mostly right, but almost everything is wrong, from the intro to the end. the last two pages aren't even the right arrangement much less the right notes

Well, maybe I should have added one thing to the description: If you are in need of maybe the most accurate transcriptions of a number of boogie woogie classics, I would suggest the transcriptions made by Colin Davey at colindavey.com
